<HEADLINE>
FT  21 JAN 92 / Kalamazoo sale realises Pounds 4.3m
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Kalamazoo, the business systems and specialist print manufacturer, has
completed the sale of its shares in Great American Software to Meca Software
for Pounds 4.3m.
That will be satisfied as to Pounds 2.6m cash, 800,000 of Meca loan notes
and 100,000 shares. A further 140,000 shares will be issued subject to the
performance of the company.
The seasonal nature of GAS's trade, combined with the depressed US economy,
meant that it would show, as a discontinued activity, a substantial loss in
Kalamazoo's interim results to January 31 1992.
Accordingly, the effect on Kalamazoo's balance sheet of the disposal was
expected to be about neutral.
</TEXT>
