The group is trying to re-establish itself as a supplier of speciality
activated carbons and solvent recovery plants after a high level of debts
forced it to sell its water treatment and environmental engineering
companies in late 1990.
Last year, in spite of the disposals, it had to refinance its debts and Mr
John Bellak, non-executive chairman, who also headed Severn Trent Water at
the time, was forced to resign.
Sutcliffe hopes that the sale of high technology carbons, which are used in
environmental applications, will support its recovery as environmental
legislation is increased.
The loss per share was significantly reduced to 1.6p (49.1p).
