FT  20 JAN 92 / Observer: Marking time
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Not content with being out of sync with Moscow politically, the Ukraine
yesterday rooted itself in a different time zone. Russia moved its clocks on
an hour in a belated attempt to compensate for short winter days, but the
Ukrainians stuck to the old time.
They are now only one hour ahead of most European countries whereas Moscow
is two hours ahead - which will please Ukrainian politicians keen to move
their country towards the west and away from their former masters.
