<HEADLINE>
FT  18 JAN 92 / Finance and the Family: More life bonuses announced
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
NPI and Royal Life announced their bonuses on life assurance policies this
week. Both followed the trend of cutting pay-outs on ten-year policies while
leaving 25-year pay-outs relatively unscathed.
Using the standard assumption of a 29-year-old man paying Pounds 30 monthly
premiums, NPI left its 25-year pay-out unchanged at Pounds 51,989, while
10-year pay-outs dipped 8.8 per cent to Pounds 6,003. Royal Life's 25-year
pay-out increased 12 per cent to Pounds 55,052, but 10-year pay-outs fell 5
per cent to Pounds 6,443.
Neither office is likely to feature among the strongest performers for the
year - for example Commercial Union is paying out Pounds 65,596 and Pounds
7,484.
