<HEADLINE>
FT  18 JAN 92 / World Commodities Prices: Spices
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Last year saw the peak in overall pepper production which was boosted after
record prices in 1987, reports Man-producten. Pepper vines have a start-up
period of about four years and once mature it is difficult to shut them
down. However, reduced fertilisation is likely to result in smaller crops in
1992. Once global stocks become manageable, prices will increase. Nutmegs -
unchanged, with somewhat firmer undertone for the better grades. Cassia -
arrivals are beginning to accumulate in New York. Cloves, pimento, ginger -
markets quiet.
