FT  18 JAN 92 / UK Company News: Aids drug sales boost Wellcome
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DANIEL GREEN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
SALES by Wellcome, the pharmaceutical group, were 20 per cent higher in the
last four months of 1991 than in the comparable period in 1990.
Sir Alastair France, the chairman, told yesterday's annual meeting that 'our
main anti-viral products, Zovirax and Retrovir, are exhibiting particularly
